### Current Performance Interpretation

The row cache is fast once loaded. The original cost came from recursive
runtime metadata digest validation, live scan rebuilds, and live parity checks.
The new opt-in fast audit path uses validation_strength=header_only,
compare_live_scan=false, and allow_unproven_cache=true. It reports
cache_used_unproven_for_audit_query=true and keeps cache_valid_for_audit_query
false, so it is explicitly not target-readiness proof.

